    "In both climacteric (Pech et al., 2008) and most of the non-climacteric fruits (Batista-Silva et al., 2018), acidity is an observable indicator of maturation.",
    "Unlike sweetness, acidity declines gradually as the fruit reaches maturity although the rate of acidity changes is affected by the cultivars and season.",
